    <h1>Factor Models</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">MIT OCW 18.S096 + 15.450 (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>factor model</strong> decomposes an asset's return into exposure to a few common risk factors plus idiosyncratic noise. If you can identify the factors, you can separate the risk you're paid for from the risk you can diversify away.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: factor decomposition diagram -->
